From: Marian Chereji <marian.chereji@freescale.com>
Date: Fri, 9 Mar 2012 20:16:30 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 113/518] Enabled sanity checks in the DPA Offload drivers

Added the build flag which enables user parameter verification
in the DPA Offload drivers.

Signed-off-by: Marian Chereji <marian.chereji@freescale.com>
[Grabbed from the branch, LINUX_IR5.2.0, of
https://git.freescale.com/git-private/cgit.cgi/ppc/alu-b4860/linux.git.]
Signed-off-by: Tiejun Chen <tiejun.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/staging/fsl_dpa_offload/Makefile |    3 ++-
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/staging/fsl_dpa_offload/Makefile b/drivers/staging/fsl_dpa_offload/Makefile
index 94352fd..7e5f46f 100644
--- a/drivers/staging/fsl_dpa_offload/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/staging/fsl_dpa_offload/Makefile
@@ -39,7 +39,8 @@ include $(srctree)/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/NetCommSw/ncsw_config.mk
 
 EXTRA_CFLAGS += \
 	-Idrivers/crypto/caam \
-	-Idrivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/NetCommSw/src/wrapper
+	-Idrivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/NetCommSw/src/wrapper \
+	-DDPA_OFFLOAD_SANITY_CHECKS
 
 obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_IPACC_USECASES)   += usecases/
 
